{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 12:51:53.774359", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\n1) Anomaly detection\n- End-to-end data-plane outage: All host-to-host pings fail, both within the same leaf and across leaves.\n  - Examples:\n    - host_1_1 -> host_1_2: Destination Host Unreachable (100% loss)\n    - host_1_1 -> host_2_1: Destination Host Unreachable (100% loss)\n    - host_2_1 -> host_2_2: Destination Host Unreachable (100% loss)\n    - host_2_2 -> host_1_2: Destination Host Unreachable (100% loss)\n- Host interfaces are up with correct IPs in 10.0.0.0/24, but no RX traffic observed (consistent with no forwarding/ARP resolution).\n\n2) Localization of faulty components\n- All OVS switches (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) are disconnected from the SDN controller and have no flows installed.\n  - ovs-ofctl dump-flows on leaf_1, leaf_2, and spine_1 returns only headers (no flow entries).\n  - ovs-vsctl list controller on all switches shows:\n    - is_connected: false\n    - status: last_error=\"Connection timed out\", state=CONNECTING\n    - target: tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\n  - All three switches are configured with fail_mode: secure.\n- Management network connectivity is healthy:\n  - leaf_1, leaf_2, and spine_1 can ping 20.0.0.100 successfully (RTT ~0.7–1.2 ms).\n  - Switch management IPs:\n    - leaf_1 eth3: 20.0.0.2/24\n    - leaf_2 eth3: 20.0.0.3/24\n    - spine_1 eth2: 20.0.0.1/24\n- Impact scope:\n  - Intra-leaf connectivity is broken (e.g., host_1_1 ↔ host_1_2), indicating local bridging not functioning due to lack of flows.\n  - Inter-leaf connectivity is also broken (e.g., host_1_1 ↔ host_2_1) for the same reason.\n\n3) Root cause analysis\n- The SDN controller at 20.0.0.100 is reachable at the IP layer (ICMP OK) but not accepting TCP connections on the configured OpenFlow port 6633:\n  - All switches report connection timed out to tcp:20.0.0.100:6633.\n  - This suggests the controller process is not listening on 6633, is down, or is using a different OpenFlow port (e.g., 6653).\n- Because all OVS bridges are in fail_mode secure and have no flow entries, traffic is dropped when the controller is unreachable. This explains:\n  - No ARP resolution on any host (hence “Destination Host Unreachable”).\n  - No L2 forwarding within or across leaves.\n- No evidence of link/interface failures on the data-plane ports themselves; data-plane ports are UP on all switches. The outage is control-plane related (OpenFlow session establishment), not physical connectivity.\n\nRelevant evidence excerpts\n- Pings:\n  - host_1_1 -> 10.0.0.2: 3 transmitted, 0 received, +3 errors, 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable”\n  - host_2_1 -> 10.0.0.4: 3 transmitted, 0 received, +3 errors, 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable”\n- OVS controller status on all switches:\n  - target \"tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\", is_connected=false, state=CONNECTING, last_error=\"Connection timed out\"\n- Flow tables:\n  - ovs-ofctl dump-flows: empty on leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1\n- Management reachability:\n  - All switches can ping 20.0.0.100 with 0% loss\n\nAssessment summary\n- Network health: Critical outage. Data-plane forwarding is entirely non-functional due to lack of OpenFlow control-plane connectivity and secure fail mode behavior.\n- Fault localization: Centralized at the SDN controller’s OpenFlow service (20.0.0.100:6633) or controller-port configuration mismatch; manifests uniformly across all OVS devices.\n- Root cause: Controller not accepting OpenFlow connections on 6633 leading to no flow programming; with fail_mode=secure, switches drop traffic, causing complete L2 connectivity loss across the fabric.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 12478, "output_tokens": 2714, "total_tokens": 15192, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 11776}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1728}}}
